Scotland's independent schools improved academic achievement records by not setting down both in 2018 and once again demonstrated outstanding exam results, which were only further enhanced by individual and collective achievements in sports, art, music and other community merits.
When there are a total of more than 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), aim to provide their students and their parents with the highest possible level of services.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen career and to be citizens of the world.
Working in the education sector, which can design and implement the school curriculum, we can see that modern languages continue to be popular and choose them willingly in schools.
Nelson Mandela said: “If you are able to speak to a person in a language he understands, he will understand you with his mind.
