Learning several languages, especially in developing countries, will improve children’s chances of meaningful employment.
In Scotland, each school varies according to the languages it teaches.
A number of schools focus on more classical modern languages, while others teach languages that are considered most important to the UK, looking to the future of 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever the interests of your child, there will always be many languages from which you can choose an independent school with teaching staff and specialists in this field.
Scottish independent schools are ready to create a training environment that prepares children and provides them with the skills they need to live in the future.
There is no denying that languages remain vital for the future of the country in today's global business environment, and this must also be reflected in the education system.
Indeed, modern languages should certainly be regarded as "international communication skills".
Independent schools will continue to offer this option, diversity and results for Scottish youth.
