"Red Flood" news. Concentration in Painell, Manati and Sarasota is falling
According to a recent report by the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission (FWC), the total concentration of "red tide" in the Tampa Bay area is decreasing.
According to the FWC, more fragmented blooms have been observed in Painelas, Manati, Sarasota, Charlotte and Colliery counties, suggesting that the concentration is declining.
The "Red Flood" bloom spans approximately 130 miles of coast from northern Painelas to southern Lee Counties.
Flowering areas can be found about 10 miles from the shore in Hillsboro County, but less than last week .
The "red flood" has also been observed in Pasco County.
Last week, concentrations in and along Painelas County were reported to be moderate, low to high along the Hillsboro County coast, in Manati County from background to high, in Sarasota County and along the coast from background to high, in Charlotte County from background to medium, along the Lee County coast from background to high, and in Colliery County to low.
There are still reports of respiratory irritation in Painelas, Manati, Sarasota, Li and Colliery counties.
There have been no reports of respiratory irritation in northwestern Florida in the past week.
